WEBVTT

00:01.234 --> 00:03.504
[theme music]

00:11.545 --> 00:14.080
♪ Sometimes the world
looks perfect ♪

00:15.248 --> 00:17.551
♪ Nothing to rearrange ♪

00:17.584 --> 00:20.554
♪ Sometimes you just
get a feeling ♪

00:20.587 --> 00:23.524
♪ Like you need
some kind of change ♪

00:24.858 --> 00:28.595
♪ No matter what the odds
are this time ♪

00:28.629 --> 00:31.064
♪ Nothing’s gonna
stand in my way ♪

00:31.097 --> 00:32.533
♪ This flame in my heart ♪

00:32.566 --> 00:34.334
♪ Like a long lost friend ♪

00:34.367 --> 00:37.804
♪ Gives every dark street
a light at the end ♪

00:39.339 --> 00:42.408
♪ Standing tall ♪

00:42.442 --> 00:46.246
♪ On the wings of my dream ♪

00:46.279 --> 00:49.282
♪ Rise and fall ♪

00:49.315 --> 00:53.153
♪ On the wings of my dream ♪

00:53.186 --> 00:56.156
♪ The rain and thunder
the wind and haze ♪

00:56.189 --> 00:59.560
♪ I’m bound for better days ♪

00:59.593 --> 01:02.829
♪ It’s my life and my dream ♪

01:02.863 --> 01:06.266
♪ And nothing’s gonna
stop me now ♪

01:15.742 --> 01:18.244
[instrumental music]

01:23.917 --> 01:25.619
(Balki)
Look at this, Ms. Lydia.

01:25.652 --> 01:27.854
I’m running for
Student Body President

01:27.888 --> 01:29.623
at the Chicago City College.

01:29.656 --> 01:32.158
Ah!
Balki, that’s terrific.

01:32.192 --> 01:33.459
‐Yeah.
‐How’s it going?

01:33.493 --> 01:35.629
Oh, just as sleazy as pie.

01:38.198 --> 01:39.499
Just like campaigning
on Mypos.

01:39.533 --> 01:41.267
All you have to do
is make sure

01:41.301 --> 01:42.803
that everyone knows
how you feel

01:42.836 --> 01:44.370
about the important issues.

01:44.404 --> 01:46.573
And I’ve already told
anyone who would listen

01:46.607 --> 01:49.109
that I’m pro‐sheep
and anti‐wolf.

01:51.545 --> 01:53.246
Coming out against wolves

01:53.279 --> 01:56.282
is a good start, Balki.

01:56.316 --> 01:58.351
But, uh, maybe you should ask
Larry to help you.

01:58.384 --> 01:59.352
Yeah.

01:59.385 --> 02:03.223
Um, actually I haven’t
told Cousin Larry

02:03.256 --> 02:05.191
that I’m, that I’m running.

02:05.225 --> 02:07.393
Oh, well, if you tell him,
I’m sure he’d help you

02:07.427 --> 02:09.461
with your campaign,
why don’t you ask him?

02:09.495 --> 02:13.466
[chuckles]
Well, because if I, uh

02:13.499 --> 02:15.669
if I ask Cousin Larry
to‐to help me

02:15.702 --> 02:18.872
with my campaign,
um, I’m sort of afraid

02:18.905 --> 02:21.742
Cousin Larry will
help me

02:21.775 --> 02:23.143
with my campaign.

02:25.712 --> 02:26.913
Uh, I don’t know
if you’ve noticed

02:26.947 --> 02:29.349
but Cousin Larry

02:29.382 --> 02:31.384
he‐he‐he’s trying
to be helpful

02:31.417 --> 02:33.520
but‐but he tends
to go overboard.

02:33.554 --> 02:36.156
He’s kind of
a type‐A personality.

02:37.758 --> 02:39.660
So, I‐I‐I beg of you

02:39.693 --> 02:42.428
please, promise me,
you won’t tell Cousin Larry?

02:42.462 --> 02:45.498
A team of wild horses
couldn’t drag it out of me.

02:45.532 --> 02:47.868
Thank you, Ms. Lydia.

02:47.901 --> 02:50.771
Of course, the sweaty cowboy
pulling the reins

02:50.804 --> 02:52.272
might have a shot.

02:57.711 --> 02:58.912
Hi, Balki.

03:00.547 --> 03:03.283
Oh, I see you’re running

03:03.316 --> 03:04.851
for Student Body President.

03:07.020 --> 03:08.488
Oh, good luck
with your campaign‐‐

03:08.522 --> 03:10.824
Cousin, now, listen to me,
no matter what you say

03:10.857 --> 03:12.759
no matter what you do,
there is absolutely

03:12.793 --> 03:15.361
no way that I’m...

03:15.395 --> 03:17.698
What did you just say?

03:17.731 --> 03:20.333
I said, "Good luck
with your campaign."

03:20.366 --> 03:22.769
Well, bang my bongos
and call me Daisy.

03:26.673 --> 03:29.242
You mean to say that, that
you’re not gonna force yourself

03:29.275 --> 03:31.377
into my campaign and,
and then go overboard

03:31.411 --> 03:33.880
and make yourself
a royal pain in the boingi?

03:36.016 --> 03:37.784
Oh!

03:37.818 --> 03:39.820
Oh, I see.

03:39.853 --> 03:43.423
I see, you‐you think
because I lost

03:43.456 --> 03:46.259
every campaign
I managed in school

03:46.292 --> 03:48.795
that I would see your campaign
as my last chance

03:48.829 --> 03:50.764
to be a winner.

03:52.699 --> 03:54.801
You lost every single campaign?

03:56.537 --> 03:59.005
Yeah, yeah, uh...
No, no, I‐I admit it.

03:59.039 --> 04:01.642
Uh, it used to bother me,
but I’m over it.

04:01.675 --> 04:05.712
Those hundred and twenty hours
of self‐help tapes cured me.

04:06.980 --> 04:09.315
I no longer have that
overwhelming need

04:09.349 --> 04:11.384
to win just once.

04:15.689 --> 04:17.057
So...good luck.

04:17.089 --> 04:19.392
I hope you win.

04:19.425 --> 04:21.494
Wait one
finger‐lickin’ moment.

04:21.528 --> 04:24.598
Are you telling me
that we can discuss this

04:24.631 --> 04:27.033
and‐and your eyes won’t
bulge out of your head

04:27.067 --> 04:30.871
and that vein in your forehead
won’t start throbbing?

04:30.904 --> 04:32.372
Oh, sure.
Oh, yeah, yeah, yeah.

04:32.405 --> 04:34.307
Oh, that syndrome
is covered in tapes

04:34.340 --> 04:37.377
one through forty‐three

04:37.410 --> 04:41.481
"Coping and being at peace
with your body."

04:41.515 --> 04:44.484
"My body is like a hollow reed.

04:44.518 --> 04:46.787
Troubles blow through me
like the wind."

04:46.820 --> 04:49.756
[inhales]

04:51.758 --> 04:52.759
[whistles]

04:59.365 --> 05:01.467
Okay.
Uh, well, cousin, I...

05:01.502 --> 05:03.637
I‐I’m glad you’ve
weathered that storm

05:03.670 --> 05:05.939
because I’d love to
tell you about my campaign.

05:05.972 --> 05:07.107
Well, I’d love to
hear about it.

05:07.140 --> 05:09.510
Well, um, if I’m elected

05:09.543 --> 05:12.012
my goal is to reinstate
the language requirement.

05:12.045 --> 05:13.580
That means
every student have to

05:13.614 --> 05:15.448
take a foreign language
to graduate.

05:15.481 --> 05:17.684
I feel that we’ll all understand
each other better

05:17.718 --> 05:20.621
if we can speak
in another man’s tongue

05:20.654 --> 05:23.724
walk in another man’s shoes

05:23.757 --> 05:26.593
see the world through
another man’s binoculars

05:28.695 --> 05:31.331
cure another man’s ham...

05:32.498 --> 05:34.901
...build with
another man’s Legos.

05:37.037 --> 05:38.805
I’m still fine‐tuning
my platform.

05:40.707 --> 05:42.843
‐You call that a platform?
‐Okay, here it is!

05:42.876 --> 05:44.010
I knew it was coming!

05:44.044 --> 05:46.813
[gibberish]

05:50.450 --> 05:52.152
No, wait, no. I‐I know.
I know.

05:52.185 --> 05:55.789
You thought that I that I was
just gonna jump in and go crazy

05:55.822 --> 05:57.824
but‐but I was only asking,
if that’s your platform.

05:57.858 --> 05:59.760
And‐and if it is...

06:00.994 --> 06:02.395
...I hope it works for you.

06:04.097 --> 06:05.365
‐Really?
‐Really.

06:06.800 --> 06:08.569
Aw, thank you, cousin.

06:08.602 --> 06:11.004
That’s, that’s not the only
weapon in my Arsenio.

06:11.037 --> 06:12.472
I haven’t even started baking

06:12.506 --> 06:14.675
my special election
spleen chip cookies.

06:14.708 --> 06:17.177
‐Spleen chip cookies?
‐Yeah, original recipe.

06:17.210 --> 06:19.145
And now with pimentos.

06:23.617 --> 06:24.951
W‐well, well...

06:40.834 --> 06:44.104
You know, Balki, uh, uh,
I‐I don’t want you to think

06:44.137 --> 06:45.906
that I’m getting involved
in your campaign

06:45.939 --> 06:47.440
because I’m not.
Really.

06:47.473 --> 06:50.677
But‐but a‐as
a disinterested bystander

06:50.711 --> 06:54.615
uh, would you allow me to say
that spleen chip cookies

06:54.648 --> 06:56.983
are not gonna be enough
to, to get you elected.

06:57.017 --> 06:58.885
Well, of course they’re not.

06:58.919 --> 07:01.187
Don’t be ridiculous.

07:01.221 --> 07:03.023
That’s why each student
gets a special

07:03.056 --> 07:05.592
"Vote for Balki"
sheep kidney coin pouch.

07:07.027 --> 07:08.494
Oh, no, no.
Don’t touch, cousin.

07:08.529 --> 07:09.996
It’s‐it’s not quite dry yet.

07:13.600 --> 07:17.938
Balki, s‐sheep kidney coin
pouches and spleen chip cookies

07:17.971 --> 07:20.674
with or without pimentos,
may work on Mypos

07:20.707 --> 07:24.210
but in America,
you‐you‐you need slogans

07:24.244 --> 07:26.246
buttons, posters,
position papers.

07:26.279 --> 07:28.248
We have got to set up
meetings with the voters.

07:28.281 --> 07:29.583
We’re gonna have to,
did I say "We?"

07:29.616 --> 07:31.518
Because I meant "You."
You.

07:33.153 --> 07:36.022
This is your campaign.
Not mine. I wouldn’t do it.

07:36.056 --> 07:37.758
[chuckles]
I put all that behind me.

07:37.791 --> 07:40.026
[chuckles]
No, no way. No how.

07:40.060 --> 07:42.028
Not in a million years.

07:42.062 --> 07:43.597
Don’t need it, don’t want it

07:43.630 --> 07:44.998
wouldn’t do it

07:45.031 --> 07:46.232
not this guy.

07:48.301 --> 07:50.003
You want in,
don’t you, cousin?

07:51.705 --> 07:53.674
[crying]
More than anything else
in the world.

07:53.707 --> 07:56.209
Please, please, please.

07:58.779 --> 08:01.281
Okay, okay. You can be
my campaign manager.

08:01.314 --> 08:03.650
Oh, thank you!
Thank you! Thank you!

08:03.684 --> 08:05.251
But you have to
promise me one thing.

08:05.285 --> 08:09.122
‐Anything.
‐You won’t go overboard.

08:09.155 --> 08:11.958
I promise
I won’t go overboard.

08:11.992 --> 08:12.993
Oh.

08:16.630 --> 08:19.566
[drum beats]

08:28.141 --> 08:30.877
[indistinct chatter]

08:37.650 --> 08:39.720
Balki, I’m glad you’re here.

08:39.753 --> 08:41.221
Let me show you
around campaign headquarters.

08:41.254 --> 08:43.724
Cousin, you said, you were
not going to go overboard.

08:43.756 --> 08:46.059
You promised me, you were
not going to go overboard.

08:46.092 --> 08:47.828
And here you are

08:47.861 --> 08:50.096
scraping barnacles
off the Titanic!

08:52.633 --> 08:55.936
Balki, this is just
a bare minimum.

08:55.969 --> 08:57.303
We have posters
with your picture

08:57.337 --> 08:58.805
we’re putting up
all over campus.

08:58.839 --> 09:00.240
We have people calling students

09:00.273 --> 09:02.142
urging them to vote for you.

09:02.175 --> 09:04.310
We have volunteers
stuffing campaign literature

09:04.344 --> 09:06.012
into envelopes.

09:06.046 --> 09:07.981
‐"Dear fellow student..."
‐No time now.

09:08.014 --> 09:09.249
You can read
what you said later.

09:09.282 --> 09:11.251
Have you noticed

09:11.284 --> 09:14.755
how handsome you look
in the poster?

09:14.788 --> 09:17.824
Oh, cousin,
it’s a real Kojak moment.

09:19.960 --> 09:22.228
Now, over here,
we are tallying

09:22.262 --> 09:24.197
the latest results
of a poll we’ve just taken.

09:24.230 --> 09:27.033
I want to know how much
of a lead I have built for you.

09:27.067 --> 09:29.269
I’m good, Balki.
I am really good.

09:30.637 --> 09:31.872
Balki, this is so exciting.

09:31.905 --> 09:34.240
You’re gonna be
Student Body President!

09:34.274 --> 09:36.777
And I’m gonna be
First Girlfriend.

09:36.810 --> 09:37.844
I’ve recruited
Jennifer and Mary Anne

09:37.878 --> 09:39.079
to help with the women’s vote.

09:39.112 --> 09:40.380
Oh, I’m gonna speak
on your behalf

09:40.413 --> 09:41.982
at the women
in College Foundation.

09:42.015 --> 09:43.617
And I’m talking
to the cheerleaders.

09:43.650 --> 09:44.685
I speak their language.

09:46.920 --> 09:49.222
‐Give me a B!
‐B!

09:49.255 --> 09:51.091
‐Give me an A!
‐A!

09:51.124 --> 09:52.793
‐Give me an L!
‐L!

09:52.826 --> 09:54.327
‐Give me a K‐‐
‐Okay, Mary Anne, that’s good.

09:54.360 --> 09:56.196
That’s good. Save it, save it,
save it for the rally.

09:59.766 --> 10:03.203
Cousin, are all
of these people

10:03.236 --> 10:04.671
going to stay to dinner?

10:04.705 --> 10:07.908
Because I‐I only made
pig snout for four

10:07.941 --> 10:10.343
and you know how hard
it is to stretch snout.

10:12.412 --> 10:14.014
Balki, they’re not
staying for dinner.

10:14.047 --> 10:16.950
These are your campaign
working volunteers.

10:16.983 --> 10:20.053
They believe in you.
They love you.

10:20.086 --> 10:21.087
[chuckles]

10:25.859 --> 10:29.162
Now, your job
is just to be yourself.

10:29.195 --> 10:31.665
Just...be Balki.

10:31.698 --> 10:34.067
‐You think you can handle that?
‐Well, of course I can.

10:34.100 --> 10:35.368
Don’t be ridiculous.

10:35.401 --> 10:37.070
I’ve got the vest, the accent

10:37.103 --> 10:38.739
and twenty‐six years
of experience.

10:39.973 --> 10:41.407
I knew you could do it.

10:41.441 --> 10:43.243
Oh, cousin,
I’m gonna need your advice.

10:43.276 --> 10:45.812
You’ve got to tell me
which vest do you think

10:45.846 --> 10:47.914
I should wear to the debate.

10:47.948 --> 10:48.982
What debate?

10:49.015 --> 10:50.283
I’ve been challenged
to a debate

10:50.316 --> 10:52.886
the day before the election,
isn’t that great?

10:52.919 --> 10:55.922
No debate! No debate!
Debates are a big mistake.

10:55.956 --> 10:57.457
But, cousin, don’t you think
it’s a good way

10:57.490 --> 10:59.926
to show the students
how I feel about the issues?

10:59.960 --> 11:01.828
I’ve got that covered.
Don’t worry about it.

11:01.862 --> 11:02.929
Have I told you how good I am?

11:02.963 --> 11:04.097
‐Twice.
‐Okay.

11:04.130 --> 11:06.933
Now, tomorrow
at ten o’clock

11:06.967 --> 11:08.702
you’ll be meeting
with the football team.

11:08.735 --> 11:10.804
You’ll tell them how important
you think sports are

11:10.837 --> 11:11.905
to the school’s image,
got it?

11:11.938 --> 11:14.207
Uh, sports are good
for school’s image. Got it.

11:14.240 --> 11:16.009
Okay, then at 10:30, you’ll be
meeting with the science club.

11:16.042 --> 11:18.111
You’ll tell them, you think
education is important

11:18.144 --> 11:20.280
and too much of the school’s
budget is spent on sports.

11:20.313 --> 11:22.382
‐Got it?
‐Too much on sports. Got it.

11:22.415 --> 11:24.250
Okay, at noon, you’ll be
meeting with the fraternities.

11:24.284 --> 11:26.319
You’ll tell them, you think
entirely too much time

11:26.352 --> 11:27.387
is being spent in the classroom

11:27.420 --> 11:28.955
and you’re pushing
for a three day weekend, got it?

11:28.989 --> 11:29.823
Too much fraternity.

11:29.856 --> 11:31.124
Then at
three o’clock you’ll be

11:31.157 --> 11:32.258
meeting with
the Honor Society.

11:32.292 --> 11:34.494
You’ll tell them, you think,
we’re here to study

11:34.528 --> 11:36.897
not to party, and you’re pushing
for Saturday classes, got it?

11:36.930 --> 11:39.933
Okay, cousin,
small, small question

11:39.966 --> 11:42.903
from a simple Mypiot boy.

11:42.936 --> 11:46.172
This looks like I’m just telling
everyone what they want to hear.

11:46.206 --> 11:47.207
Welcome to politics.

11:49.409 --> 11:52.412
I am so proud of you.

11:52.445 --> 11:54.380
Now, cousin,
just hold on a moment.

11:54.414 --> 11:57.417
Are you asking me
to do something dishonest?

11:57.450 --> 11:59.019
B‐but, Balki,
you‐you want to

11:59.052 --> 12:00.253
reinstate the language
requirement, don’t you?

12:00.286 --> 12:02.455
‐Yes.
‐Well, to do that.

12:02.488 --> 12:04.190
You’re gonna have to get elected
Student Body President

12:04.224 --> 12:06.126
and I am the man
to help you do it.

12:06.159 --> 12:07.794
Cousin, I think
I can make my position

12:07.828 --> 12:10.030
on all the issues
clear at the debate.

12:10.063 --> 12:11.932
No debate!
Forget the debate!

12:11.965 --> 12:15.101
First rule of campaigning,
do not debate!

12:15.135 --> 12:18.539
Uh, Larry I have the results
of the latest poll.

12:18.572 --> 12:19.973
Attention!
Attention, everybody!

12:20.006 --> 12:21.508
We have the results
of the latest poll.

12:21.542 --> 12:23.510
Go ahead, Jennifer.
Give them the good news.

12:23.544 --> 12:24.444
‐Cousin, I‐‐
‐Uh, Larry, I think we should‐‐

12:24.477 --> 12:26.212
I think you’re wrong
about the debate.

12:26.246 --> 12:28.982
Balki, for the last time,
no debate! No debate!

12:29.015 --> 12:30.183
Go ahead, Jennifer.

12:30.216 --> 12:33.019
Tell them how far
Balki is ahead.

12:33.053 --> 12:35.188
Balki is trailing
by fifteen points.

12:37.824 --> 12:39.492
You’re gonna have to
debate your opponent.

12:45.966 --> 12:48.268
[instrumental music]

12:51.471 --> 12:53.807
[indistinct chatter]

12:53.840 --> 12:56.943
Balki, for the last time

12:56.977 --> 12:58.444
you are not going to wear

12:58.478 --> 13:02.215
the traditional
Myposian election hat!

13:02.248 --> 13:04.350
(Balki)
’Oh, is that so, is that?’

13:04.384 --> 13:05.519
‐Give it to me!
‐’No!’

13:05.552 --> 13:06.587
‐Give it to me!
‐’No!’

13:06.620 --> 13:08.288
Give it to me!

13:18.031 --> 13:20.967
[babbling]

13:22.035 --> 13:23.970
[panting]

13:25.271 --> 13:28.041
Jennifer, Mary Anne

13:28.074 --> 13:30.310
Balki is ready
for the mock debate.

13:30.343 --> 13:33.246
I’ve groomed him,
I’ve prepared him.

13:33.279 --> 13:34.615
It’s taken five years
off my life.

13:34.648 --> 13:37.584
[sobbing]

13:39.219 --> 13:41.454
Oh, ladies...

13:42.255 --> 13:44.057
...here he is

13:44.090 --> 13:46.593
the next
Student Body President

13:46.627 --> 13:48.595
of Chicago City College

13:48.629 --> 13:50.363
Balki Bartokomous.

13:50.396 --> 13:53.199
[applause]

13:58.204 --> 14:00.373
Oh, Balki, you look
so handsome in that suit.

14:02.208 --> 14:04.010
It needs a hat.

14:06.647 --> 14:08.582
It doesn’t need a hat.

14:13.186 --> 14:16.590
Okay, ladies,
take your seats.

14:16.623 --> 14:18.925
Now, Balki...

14:18.959 --> 14:21.227
[panting]

14:21.261 --> 14:24.164
Remember, ahem,
presentation is key...

14:24.197 --> 14:25.231
Right.

14:25.265 --> 14:26.099
...to winning the debate.

14:26.132 --> 14:28.234
Okay? Right, alright?
Okay? Alright?

14:28.268 --> 14:30.904
Well, what do we do
to improve our presentation?

14:30.937 --> 14:34.340
Um...
Oh! Oh!

14:34.374 --> 14:36.610
I don’t rest my hands
on the podium.

14:36.643 --> 14:38.679
It makes me look lazy.

14:38.712 --> 14:41.582
‐And, uh... Uh, and...
‐Uh, uh, uh, uh...

14:41.615 --> 14:44.117
Oh! And I don’t
fidget with my tie.

14:44.150 --> 14:46.987
It, uh, it makes me
look, uh, nervous.

14:47.020 --> 14:48.054
Uh‐huh.
What else?

14:49.322 --> 14:50.356
Heck if I know.

14:50.390 --> 14:53.126
[grunts]

14:53.159 --> 14:56.162
Oh! I never use the‐the phrase,
"Heck if I know."

14:56.196 --> 14:59.265
It makes me sound,
it makes me sound chloroformed.

15:00.734 --> 15:02.268
