15:49.683 --> 15:52.385
Mr. Bartokomous,
what is your position

15:52.418 --> 15:55.055
on the financing
of student loans?

15:55.088 --> 15:59.192
Jennifer, uh, uh, I’m glad
you asked me that question

15:59.225 --> 16:02.195
because the financing
of student loans

16:02.228 --> 16:05.999
um, is‐is an issue
that deserves my attention

16:06.032 --> 16:08.434
and, uh, and, uh,
let me assure you

16:08.468 --> 16:12.105
that my attention
is what it will receive

16:12.138 --> 16:15.441
in‐in its complete
and unabridged form.

16:15.475 --> 16:18.211
Uh, and‐and the financing
of student loans

16:18.244 --> 16:21.447
is actually part of,
uh, of my...

16:21.481 --> 16:24.250
...ten point program
for better schooling.

16:24.284 --> 16:26.019
Yes, Balki,
you are doing great!

16:26.052 --> 16:27.621
‐Oh!
‐Ah! Ah!

16:27.654 --> 16:29.222
Smile.

16:30.757 --> 16:32.693
[instrumental music]

16:39.332 --> 16:41.401
Larry, I have to talk to you,
I have something to tell you

16:41.434 --> 16:42.803
that’s going to upset you.

16:42.836 --> 16:44.304
You’ve changed your mind.

16:44.337 --> 16:46.406
You‐you’re not gonna marry me?

16:46.439 --> 16:48.775
That’s awful!
You didn’t tell me that!

16:50.811 --> 16:53.113
That’s not the bad news.

16:53.146 --> 16:55.381
Well, maybe not to you,
but think of poor Larry.

16:57.483 --> 16:58.752
Larry, the bad...

17:00.253 --> 17:01.822
Larry, it’s not
about the marriage.

17:01.855 --> 17:03.790
Oh!

17:03.824 --> 17:06.492
Thank God.

17:06.527 --> 17:08.261
The bad news is
the athletes found out

17:08.294 --> 17:10.463
about Balki’s plan to reinstate
the language requirement.

17:10.496 --> 17:13.398
They’ve switched their votes
to Balki’s opponent.

17:13.433 --> 17:14.701
Alright, I thought
this might happen

17:14.734 --> 17:15.801
I gotta tell Balki.

17:19.540 --> 17:22.442
Come on, Mary Anne,
we better take our seats.

17:22.474 --> 17:24.444
You know, it’s a good thing
Larry has this campaign

17:24.477 --> 17:26.780
to take his mind
off the broken engagement.

17:28.615 --> 17:30.651
Balki?

17:30.684 --> 17:32.385
The athletes have decided
to change their votes

17:32.418 --> 17:34.220
to your opponent.

17:34.254 --> 17:36.322
Well, people change
their minds.

17:36.356 --> 17:38.291
Pigs, on the other hand,
make one decision

17:38.324 --> 17:40.694
and stick with it.

17:40.727 --> 17:42.328
[snorts]

17:42.362 --> 17:43.396
Balki, don’t you understand?

17:43.429 --> 17:45.732
If we don’t get them
to change their votes back

17:45.766 --> 17:47.701
we’re going to
lose the election.

17:47.734 --> 17:50.136
Now I have an easy fix,
all we have to do is

17:50.170 --> 17:51.738
lose the language thing
and they’ll switch back to us.

17:51.772 --> 17:54.140
Cousin, wait a minute.
Are you...

17:54.174 --> 17:56.176
You know sometimes,
I think

17:56.209 --> 17:58.478
you’re just a few grapes
shy of a bunch.

17:58.512 --> 18:00.313
Have you been listening?

18:00.346 --> 18:01.748
I cannot lose
the language thing.

18:01.782 --> 18:03.684
That’s the reason
I’m running for president.

18:03.717 --> 18:05.752
I cannot give that up.

18:05.786 --> 18:07.854
Balki, your goal
is to get elected.

18:07.888 --> 18:09.523
Tell them what
they want to hear.

18:09.556 --> 18:10.857
Once you’re elected,
you can do whatever you want.

18:10.891 --> 18:13.126
Cousin, isn’t that
just a bit dishonest?

18:13.159 --> 18:14.360
It’s the American way.

18:17.197 --> 18:18.632
But won’t
the students mind?

18:18.665 --> 18:20.734
Mind?
They expect it!

18:20.767 --> 18:21.835
Wait a minute...

18:21.868 --> 18:23.269
Uh, preceding the debate

18:23.303 --> 18:24.470
there will be
an opening statement

18:24.505 --> 18:27.140
and a short period
of questions and answers

18:27.173 --> 18:28.875
by each candidate.

18:28.909 --> 18:31.812
Uh, Mr. Bartokomous, we’re ready
for your opening statement.

18:46.693 --> 18:51.431
Uh, thank you,
my fair chair lady

18:51.464 --> 18:54.801
faculty and my worthy opponent

18:54.835 --> 18:55.836
and students.

18:57.303 --> 18:59.806
My name is Balki Bartokomous

18:59.840 --> 19:02.442
of the students,
for the students

19:02.475 --> 19:03.710
by the students.

19:03.744 --> 19:05.512
Ah! Ah!

19:05.546 --> 19:06.547
Ee...

19:11.618 --> 19:13.854
Uh, if elected, I promise

19:13.887 --> 19:17.257
to be firm, yet flexible

19:17.290 --> 19:19.893
tough, yet vulnerable

19:19.926 --> 19:22.262
soft, yet absorbent.

19:29.435 --> 19:33.840
I would like to establish
a kinder, gentler cafeteria.

19:33.874 --> 19:36.810
[applause]

19:38.244 --> 19:39.613
We will now open the floor

19:39.646 --> 19:41.414
to questions
for Mr. Bartokomous.

19:44.317 --> 19:47.353
Uh, yes, in the pink angora.

19:47.387 --> 19:48.488
My name is Lisa Morgan.
Mr. Bar‐‐

19:48.522 --> 19:50.323
Hi, Lisa!

19:50.356 --> 19:51.725
Hi.

19:51.758 --> 19:52.826
Mr. Bartokomous

19:52.859 --> 19:55.495
when you spoke in front
of the Honor’s Society

19:55.529 --> 19:58.464
you said you wanted to be
the Education President.

19:58.498 --> 20:00.901
But when you spoke
in front of the fraternities

20:00.934 --> 20:03.537
you said education
was overrated.

20:03.570 --> 20:04.705
Where do you stand?

20:04.738 --> 20:06.807
I’m glad you,
you asked that question

20:06.840 --> 20:09.776
because where I stand

20:09.810 --> 20:12.679
uh, deserves my attention.

20:12.713 --> 20:16.349
And I can assure you
that where I stand

20:16.382 --> 20:17.818
’will receive my attention’

20:17.851 --> 20:20.486
in its complete
and unabridged form.

20:21.888 --> 20:23.456
‐Good answer.
‐Um, wait a minute.

20:23.489 --> 20:24.725
That doesn’t seem
to make any sense to‐‐

20:24.758 --> 20:27.327
‐Next question!
‐Hey, I got a question!

20:27.360 --> 20:28.829
What about the rumor
that you want us to take

20:28.862 --> 20:30.831
some dumb language
before we graduate?

20:32.365 --> 20:33.433
I’m glad you asked
that question

20:33.466 --> 20:35.669
because I cannot lie to you.

20:35.702 --> 20:37.303
‐Now, let me just‐‐
‐Uh, uh, yes. Uh...

20:37.337 --> 20:40.006
Uh, Mr. Bartokomous cannot lie
and he cannot stay.

20:40.040 --> 20:41.307
He has another engagement.

20:41.341 --> 20:42.375
Which is why
I’m here to tell you

20:42.408 --> 20:43.710
that, uh, if elected...

20:43.744 --> 20:44.945
Cousin, please.

20:44.978 --> 20:46.713
Please, I have to do this.

20:52.418 --> 20:54.354
Listen, if you’re
going to vote for me

20:54.387 --> 20:55.556
you’ve got to know who I am

20:55.589 --> 20:57.490
and what I really believe in.

20:57.524 --> 20:59.560
My name is Balki Bartokomous

20:59.593 --> 21:02.462
and I’m a sheepherder
from Mypos.

21:02.495 --> 21:04.765
And yes, if I am elected
I do intend

21:04.798 --> 21:06.733
to reinstate
the language requirement.

21:06.767 --> 21:09.703
[booing]

21:12.038 --> 21:14.775
[instrumental music]

