I lost, Balki.

21:28.522 --> 21:30.390
I lost big.

21:31.925 --> 21:35.529
You know, I wanted
to win just once.

21:35.562 --> 21:37.430
Cousin, would you
please stop this?

21:37.463 --> 21:38.565
You did not lose.

21:38.599 --> 21:41.434
I lost. I lost. I did.

21:41.467 --> 21:43.036
I lost the election.

21:45.471 --> 21:46.773
You’re right, Balki.

21:49.075 --> 21:50.544
You’re the big loser.

21:54.815 --> 21:56.416
And don’t you forget it.

22:00.954 --> 22:03.790
I‐I can’t believe
you’re taking this so well.

22:03.824 --> 22:04.858
You lost.

22:04.891 --> 22:06.793
But, cousin,
I did not lose.

22:06.827 --> 22:08.562
I‐I didn’t get
elected president

22:08.595 --> 22:09.896
but I got what I wanted.

22:09.930 --> 22:11.397
My opponent thought

22:11.431 --> 22:12.999
that reinstating
the language requirement

22:13.033 --> 22:14.935
was a good idea
and she’s gonna push for it.

22:16.436 --> 22:17.671
And that makes you happy?

22:17.704 --> 22:19.039
Happy?

22:19.072 --> 22:20.874
I’m erratic!

22:25.478 --> 22:27.080
‐Oh, God!
‐Oh, goodness!

22:27.113 --> 22:29.516
‐I lost again!
‐Oh, no.

22:29.550 --> 22:31.752
I’ve lost thirteen
student elections

22:31.785 --> 22:33.854
